# Phase 41: Ecosystem Reality & Algorithmic Growth

## Problem Statement
The app needs to feel "alive" on day one. Videos shouldn't have 0 views when posted, and we need a clear guide on how to manage 100 test accounts. Furthermore, videos need privacy controls (Public/Private), and remaining mock data in areas like Studio or Explore must be eradicated.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - The 100-user account ceiling requires a Supabase Service Role Key or an upgraded tier due to the 3-email-per-hour limit on the free tier. I will provide the script and the guide on how to bypass this.
> - The Algorithmic View system uses a deterministic time-based math function seeded by the video ID. This ensures organic-looking growth (e.g., 427 views) without a backend cron job. Real views will be added on top of this.

## Proposed Changes

### [Core] User Ecosystem & Guide
#### [NEW] [README.md](file:///C:/GOLive/README.md)
- Complete guide covering: Admin strategies, 100-account generation script execution, default passwords, and how to use them cross-platform.

