### [Features] Algorithmic Views & Mock Data Removal
#### [MODIFY] [utils.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/utils.ts)
- Create `calculateAlgorithmicViews(videoId, createdAt)` function.
- Math: Immediately base between 100-300 + time-decay growth + actual DB views. Avoid even numbers (e.g., 100, 500) using a string-hash of the `videoId`.

#### [MODIFY] [VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- Display calculated views.

#### [MODIFY] [app/studio/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/page.tsx)
- Remove hardcoded "(Mock)" strings. Connect likes/comments to algorithmic approximations or actual DB relationships.

## Verification Plan
1. Create a public video and verify views start > 100, ending in organic numbers (e.g., 143).
2. Create a private video and verify it does NOT show on Home or Trending.
3. Verify the [README.md](file:///C:/GOLive/README.md) is complete and clear.
